## Ring Settings for a 1 Carat Emerald Cut Diamond

[![Petite emerald cut solitaire in 14K white gold — four prong setting for 1ct diamond](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioSuperImposeBox/Rings/505031/505031_M1_EMR_DIM_wht_0100CT_W_Box2_004_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/rings/petite-emerald-cut-solitaire-diamond-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-311195?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

Settings for a 1ct emerald cut run from [$690](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/rings/petite-emerald-cut-solitaire-diamond-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-by-james-allen-item-311196?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) for a petite four-prong solitaire to [$4,625](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/bezel-set-emerald-cut-side-stone-diamond-engagement-ring-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-304637?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) for a platinum bezel with emerald cut side stones. At 1ct, the solitaire is the right proportional match — the stone at 6.5mm × 5mm is not large enough to justify a wide, heavy setting that would visually dwarf it.

A pavé band works well at 1ct if the pavé stones are small enough to not compete with the center stone. The [$1,325 petite micropavé](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/petite-micropave-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-1-10-ct-tw-item-195402?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the right scale. The [$2,090 common prong pavé](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/common-prong-diamond-pave-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-310923?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) works too but the melee stones are more prominent — watch that the band doesn't outshine the center stone at this size.

