## The 1ct Step-Up Problem

The 1ct price point in lab-grown diamonds is unusual compared to other carat weights. In natural, 1ct is the most popular size and commands a strong premium — buyers pay specifically for the 1ct number. In lab, the 1ct premium has been compressed almost entirely.

This creates what experienced buyers call the 1ct step-up opportunity: the same budget that buys a natural 1ct ring can buy a lab 2ct ring. The decision isn't natural 1ct versus lab 1ct. It's natural 1ct versus lab 2ct.

[![Emerald cut diamond ring in yellow gold pavé setting — 2ct-equivalent size at 1ct natural price](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioPackshotBox/Rings/505082/505082_M1_EMR_DIM_wht_0100CT_Y_Box3_003_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?MetalType=all&Diamonds=Dia&ShapeID=Emerald&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

Here is what different total budgets actually buy:

