The table shows the core issue: at every natural 1ct ring budget level, the lab alternative delivers a stone that is 85–100% heavier for the same or less money. This is not a close comparison. It's a structural difference driven by how lab pricing has evolved at this carat weight.

The exception is the buyer for whom natural origin is the criterion — the stone came from the earth, not a reactor. That value is real and valid. But it is the only argument for a natural 1ct emerald cut ring at current prices.

